reviews.text: Unfortunately they’ve gone down hill a little. The promos they send out got better but the prices also went up and the quality went down. It took 30 minutes for us to get a meal size salad, pasta dish and side of meatballs last night. We sent the salad back because dressing was supposed to be in the side but 25 minutes later we had to ask them to forget about it and give us the check. When our waiter asked the cook to remake the salad he loudly said “are you serious man!? What’s up with this” making us uncomfortable with the situation. We got a piece of cake to go but it was dry and the pasta portion was tiny for $15 and included burnt sausage. It was still decent overall and the roles can’t be beat. I really hope they improve

First time dining here after living in Andover for almost a year. I have to say that I was pleasantly surprised. 

Before going here, I saw online that Bertucci's (the corporation) had declared chapter 11 bankruptcy protection, and despite having just 58 locations, owed $119 million to suppliers and lenders. So, yeah, each location was, on average, about two million dollars in debt. For a tiny restaurant on main street, this was surprising to me, and I thought it would bode poorly for their service. 

I ended up coming in because I received a coupon in the mail (no idea how they got my address) offering me fifteen dollars off my purchase of 35 dollars or more. I realized that if I spent exactly 35 dollars, this would come out to an impressive 42% discount. But that percentage discount would go down the more I ordered, so I was keen on the bill being as close to 35 dollars as possible. 

I bring my date to the restaurant, and I was impressed by the interior. You have a view of the brick oven and the people preparing your food -- it was nice and transparent. We both order pizzas, she also orders a drink. While we're waiting, the waiter brings out bread with an awesome olive oil dipping blend, and I saw the bread come out of an oven about ten minutes before we were served. For a chain, they're definitely putting the effort in to make good food. This isn't Olive Garden. 

Our pizzas come out and they look awesome, with some nice charring around the edge, the crust slightly misshapen (meaning it was indeed handmade). My date ordered one with prosciutto and fig, which was one of the best tasting pizzas I've ever had, very delicate and expertly cooked, also looked amazing. Impressive it was as cheap as it was. I received the wrong pizza, though. But the waiter realized this mistake before I could comment on it, and brought me out the correct pizza without me having to ask. So I got a free pizza, which ironically I ended up liking more than the one I had actually ordered. 

At this point, our bill was only 26 dollars, so I ordered a ten dollar dessert (tiramisu) which was among the best I've ever had. The bill came out to 36 dollars, with an additional free pizza, so 21 dollars after the coupon, so after splitting the check, about 11 dollars (not including tip) for a meal with appetizer, drink, free pizza, and dessert.  It's funny, because if I hadn't had the coupon, we would have paid 26 dollars as our bill, but knowing I had this coupon, I ordered a new item, but this actually made our bill less than it would have been if I hadn't ordered more food, because the coupon kicked in. So the coupon pretty much led to them giving me more food for less money. 

This is a great place, I recommend it. It's easy to see why they're going bankrupt, this meal should easily have cost me over 25 dollars. They're giving out free appetizers and pizzas left and right with 42% discount coupons. I'll definitely be back.

I had not been to a Bertucci's restaurant in more than 15 years, but our visit back to New England brought back many memories of great meals for the past. They have added quite a few things to keep their menu up to date, but at its core the best thing is still their wood fired pizza. Loved it as always. I hope I make it back soon.

The service here is terrible. Slow doesn’t even describe it adequately. And the staff complain about their job openly throughout the dining room! The quality of Bertuccis (anywhere) just does not seem like they train the staff or management. I’ve tried 4 Bertuccis in the area hoping for a good meal. They all suck. Every last one of them should close their doors permanently.

We were the first people in the place at lunch and it took 45 min for a kids pizza and two lunch sandwiches? Forget it! Never again.
I love this location its beautiful and in a great area the food is always at its best from here by far my favorite Bertucci's location.

Beautiful rose garden, well maintained. Do come on weekends. Its located in sector 15. Space for car parking also available. You can enjoy coconut water, various flavor of ice creams, lemon soda. Best time to visit is in evening as it glows various colour full lights there. Lot of fountains with ample sitting space. Best for jogging yoga exercise, whatever you love to do.

The Rose Garden as the name suggest has different varieties of roses white , red, Yellow, orange,pink with a specific scientific name written...
The sizes of roses are also very Big.
The park is large and spread over 30 acres..
The garden is well maintained with good grass..
The trees also beautiful..
It also has a fountain..

Good to spend time here
Moreover eating facilities and washrooms are also available..
A Nala passes in between the park and has bridge to cross over it..

My mom used to come here when she lived in Chandigarh for a while. When I visited, it was nice. However, i noticed that the water (lake) was drained. It did not look very aesthetic. Wish they were fixing it at a different time. The flowers look very beautiful. If you are in Chandigarh, I recommend visiting this garden. It is also a great place for studying or reading (or relaxing in general). I just want to put out a request for people to not damage the flowers and plants. If you are taking photos, please be aware of your surroundings. This is a beautiful place, and we should keep it this way.

Visited during summer vacations and hardly found any rose. Summer definitely not the right time to visit the garden. There is not much greenery also to sit during summer. Recommended for other seasons. Kids did not enjoy much and all we could see was little squirrel 🐿 at entrance. Must be much better place during season other than summer.

Opened in 1967, this place has been one of the scenic beauty types place where you can visit anytime for nice views. The garden is well managed by the managing body. Also if you are one who is very fond of roses and would like to take a look at different varieties of roses, then this is the place for you. Also during the time of valentine's week, there is a rose festival organised here. So visit this place during this time and you will definitely worth it. For the rest of the year, this place is chic and quiet. So a good place for finding peaceful environment for a short time in a day or so
Good food in an exceptionally clean restaurant. A step up to the traditional fast food operations. Closed on Sunday!
Love the food and atmosphere at all their locations. It's refreshing to hear Christian music in the background.
Very good Cobb salad except for the almost frozen eggs.... But with out it is great. Juicy chicken and fresh green mix and a good cold lemonade... Mmmm just great.

The food here is reall good. The staff are friendly and service is fairly fast. There is plenty of parking on site. They have a nice selection of food too. Inside the restaurant there is a section for the kids to play.  The place is clean and has a very welcoming atmophere.
Yummy yummy in my tummy & my two daughters tummies. They LOVE this place.  I do too.  They got me in this place.  Wonderful customer service.  I love the atmosphere every time.

Chipotle has been my favorite restaurant since I was little. I've always remembered going to this restaurant and this food chain. I absolutely love this restaurant so much! I have never had a problem with any of the staff before and I've always had friendly young staff. The only thing that I have to say about Chipotle as a whole is about the lemon crisis. LOL. They used to have a container for the lemons and now they changed it to you having to ask for the lemons and they are given to you in a plastic container. I definitely think that that is a bad idea! I think that they should change it back to the way used to be. I'm just imagining all of the plastic tiny containers floating the ocean. That is the only reason why I would rate this a four-star rather than a five star

Good tasting food, you see it made before your eyes, add chips and guacamole to have with that HUGE burrito, a beer... really good and satisfying. However, and it's a big one, I stood in line at lunch way too long, paid way more than I expected, had just a short time to eat. I could have gone to a nice nearby restaurant, sat down with my friends, ordered without pressure and had it served while we had a good time. Just a thought....

Very well organized the food is great kind of feels like you're going through a cattle drive though they do push you through kind of fast doesn't leave much margin for error best know what you want before you get up to the counter.

Chipolte is the safe bet to fast mexican food.   While I wouldn't consider Chipolte cheap, it isn't expensive IMO.  My only slight complaint is that they treat their Guac like it was personally made by Aztec Gods who hand picked the avocados.  Its good....but not change your life great.

Chipotle never has plain white rice. I'm allergic to Cilantro and when I ask for plain white rice they look at me like I'm crazy! And the cooks want nothing to do with accommodating me. Even after talking with the store Manager and having them tell me they should fix whatever I order to my liking or needs.
Wish this could be something that all Chipotle restaurants would carry on a regular basis for those of us with allergies.
Wow, great service, great food, and great environment. Fresh food prepared well. Steak was cooked perfect. Beers are cold. Worth the price and come back often.

I thought serving bison was a little gimmicky but I had the bison pot roast and it was good. Real home made mashed potatoes were good too. I thought the gravy was only so-so, probably made from a mix and not from scratch. The service was fair, did not understand the options for bread, etc, and didn't get served any bread at all. Which kind of sucked. May or may not eat there again or at another Ted's, done the bison thing and really don't need to repeat it.
The Waiter was cordial and professional. The quality of the Prime Rib was substandard. It was not edible. We have enjoyed other meals there but doubt that we will be returning.
Real, authentic, Midwestern cuisine. Truly captures the American spirit that this country needs more of. Go for the buffalo!
Great burgers. First time I had a bison burger and it was awesome.
